13/10/2004
STRASBOURG, France -- The president of the Council of Europe (CoE) Congress, Giovanni di Stasi, said Tuesday (12 October) that fighting corruption is the core of political stability and development in Southeast European countries. 
Summarising the results of a two-day forum in the Serbia-Montenegro town of Budva, di Stasi said participants agreed on the need for better implementation of CoE anti-corruption instruments, as well as for increased training and technical assistance. 
(CoE Web site - 12/10/04)
